request.description:
### Request

- **Method**: `PUT`

- **URL**: `{{baseUrl}}/api/checkout/pub/orderForm/{{orderFormId}}/customFields`

- **Authentication**: Requires `VtexIdclientAutCookie` in the headers.


Creates or updates custom fields in the orderForm in batch.

#### Path Parameters

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| orderFormId | integer | true | Unique identifier for a customer's shopping cart. |

### Request Body

``` json
[
    {
        "linkedEntity": {
            "type": "order"
        },
        "fields": [
            {
                "name": "PO Number",
                "value": "PO1",
                "refId": "88c4c1e6-1db4-4a13-aa96-e79daba7772d"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "linkedEntity": {
            "type": "address",
            "id": "FCDEC51EDF2B4BBFA7E899CD4CA5333C"
        },
        "fields": [
            {
                "name": "Location",
                "value": "DSK1",
                "refId": "ff84f2fd-9fe1-48a0-aab2-1e0988e3e889"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "linkedEntity": {
            "type": "item",
            "id": "B2949D0A45244825B177D2F9F96DC711"
        },
        "fields": [
            {
                "name": "Cost Center",
                "value": "CC3",
                "refId": "1dd9eeb8-23ed-42b3-8028-dc7745c01ada"
            }
        ]
    }
]

 ```

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| linkedEntity | object | true | Data entity information. |
| linkedEntity{ }.type | string | true | Data entity type. |
| linkedEntity{ }.id | string | false | Data entity ID. It is required when the entity type is `address`, but can be omitted for `item` and `order`, because the system considers the current values in the orderForm. |
| fields\[ \] | array of objects | true | List with information about the custom field created or updated in the orderForm. |
| fields\[ \]{ }.name | string | true | Custom field name. |
| fields\[ \]{ }.value | string | true | Custom field value. |
| fields\[ \]{ }.refId | string | true | A reference ID that can be used to tie the custom field to external providers. For example, a Cost Center ID. |

### Response

#### Success Response

- **Status Code**: `200 OK`

- **Body**: The response will be the orderForm updated.


``` json
{
   "customData":{
      ...,
      "customFields":[
         {
            "linkedEntity":{
               "type":"item",
               "id":"B2949D0A45244825B177D2F9F96DC711"
            },
            "fields":[
                {
                    "name": "Cost Center",
                    "value": "CC3",
            "refId": "1dd9eeb8-23ed-42b3-8028-dc7745c01ada"
                }
            ]
         }
      ]
   },
   ...
}

 ```

| Field | Type | Nullable | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| linkedEntity | object | false | Data entity information. |
| linkedEntity{ }.type | string | false | Data entity type, which can be one of the following: `order` `item` `address` |
| linkedEntity{ }.id | string | true | Data entity ID. This field is nullable when the entity type is `order`. |
| fields\[ \] | array of objects | false | List with information about the custom field created or updated in the orderForm. |
| fields\[ \]{ }.name | string | false | Custom field name. |
| fields\[ \]{ }.value | string | false | Custom field value. |
| fields\[ \]{ }.refId | string | true | A reference ID that can be used to tie the custom field to external providers. For example, a Cost Center ID. |

Retrieves the default values for a specific organization unit in the VTEX Data Entity by making a GET request.

---

### Request

- **Method**: `GET`

- **URL**: `https://{{accountName}}.myvtex.com/api/dataentities/defaultValues/documents/orgUnitId-{{unit}}?_schema=v1&_fields=id,defaultValues`

- **Authentication**: Requires `VtexIdclientAutCookie` in the headers.


This request does not require a request body.

---

### Response

#### Success Response

- **Status Code**: `200 OK`


```json
{
    "id": "a6d958c2-25ba-4f4d-9a0a-6b56e458426c",
    "defaultValues": [
        {
            "entity": "address/shipping",
            "entityValueId": "cf6b85ab9-8e0a-4e49-9f1a-b48286c913a4"
        },
        {
            "entity": "address/billing",
            "entityValueId": "f6b85ab9-8e0a-4e49-9f1a-b48286c913a4"
        },
        {
            "entity": "creditCard",
            "entityValueId": "e5a80ff0-c243-4258-a2b1-f93492af46ec"
        }
    ]
}

 ```

