request.description:
This endpoint creates a new authorization dimension with its associated rules.

Dimensions contain an `unitId` field that allows grouping of dimensions by units or business areas, enabling more granular authorization control. This field is automatically filled based on the unit relative to the user creating the dimension.

If you make this request using an appKey/appToken pair, you must explicitly send the `unitId` field in the request body root.

---

### Request

- **Method**: `POST`

- **URL**: `https://api.vtexcommercestable.com.br/{{accountName}}/authorization-dimensions`

- **Authentication**: Requires `VtexIdclientAutCookie` in the headers.

- **Content-Type**: `application/json`


#### Request body

``` json
{
    "name": "Dynamic dimension with OpenTextField vtexcommercestable",
    "requireAllRulesAcceptance": true,
    "unitId": "654c12d6-6b22-4483-rt83-eb0865sdf88e",
    "priority": 1,
    "ruleCollection": [
        {
            "name": "Approve title",
            "priority": 1,
            "trigger": {
                "condition": {
                    "conditionType": 2,
                    "description": "Approve condition description",
                    "expression": "openTextField.value = '\''approved'\''"
                },
                "effect": {
                    "description": "Approve condition description",
                    "effectType": 0
                }
            },
            "scoreInterval": {
                "accept": 51,
                "deny": 49
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Deny title",
            "priority": 1,
            "trigger": {
                "condition": {
                    "conditionType": 2,
                    "description": "Deny condition description",
                    "expression": "openTextField.value = '\''denied'\''"
                },
                "effect": {
                    "description": "Deny condition description",
                    "effectType": 1
                }
            },
            "scoreInterval": {
                "accept": 51,
                "deny": 49
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Pending title",
            "authorizationData": {
                "authorizers": [
                    {
                        "type": "unit",
                        "id": "0aac12d6-6b22-4483-bd83-eb086c42888e"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "priority": 3,
            "trigger": {
                "condition": {
                    "conditionType": 2,
                    "description": "Pending condition description",
                    "expression": "openTextField.value = '\''pending'\''"
                },
                "effect": {
                    "description": "Pending condition description",
                    "effectType": 2
                }
            },
            "scoreInterval": {
                "accept": 51,
                "deny": 49
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Sequential approval title",
            "priority": 3,
            "trigger": {
                "condition": {
                    "conditionType": 2,
                    "description": "Sequential approval condition description",
                    "expression": "openTextField.value = '\''sequential-approval'\''"
                },
                "effect": {
                    "description": "Sequential approval condition description",
                    "effectType": 2
                }
            },
            "scoreInterval": {
                "accept": 51,
                "deny": 49
            },
            "authorizationData": {
                "requireAllApprovals": true,
                "authorizers": [
                    {
                        "id": "0aac12d6-6b22-4483-bd83-eb086c42888e",
                        "type": "Unit"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "5c969024-5c87-40f6-a89a-01172c5ae363",
                        "type": "User"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}

 ```

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `name` | `string` | Yes | Name of the dimension. |
| `requireAllRulesAcceptance` | `boolean` | Yes | Whether all listed rules must be accepted. If false, the first rule aproval would cause the dimension to be aproved. Always `true` for ODP. |
| `unitId` | `string` | No | Identifier of the organization unit this dimension belongs to. Each unit can have one dimension. This field is required when using `appKey/appToken` authentication. |
| `priority` | `number` | Yes | Priority of the dimension. Defines the order of application: lower numbers are evaluated first. Since each unit has a single dimension, this value is fixed as 1 by default. |
| `ruleCollection` | `array of objects` | Yes | List of rules that define conditions and actions. |
| └─ `name` | `string` | Yes | Name of the rule. |
| └─ `priority` | `number` | Yes | Rule priority. Lower numbers are evaluated first. evaluation. |
| └─ `trigger` | `object` | Yes | Defines the condition and effect that trigger the rule. |
| └─ `condition` | `object` | Yes | Condition that must be met to trigger the rule. |
| └─── `conditionType` | `number` | Yes | Type of condition. For ODP, type `2` is recommended, because it can deal with many different use cases. Type `2` defines that the rule condition is set by an expression (see field `expression`). |
| └─── `description` | `string` | Yes | Description of the condition. |
| └─── `expression` | `string` | Yes | Expression that defines the condition logic. |
| └── `effect` | `object` | Yes | Effect to apply when the condition is met. |
| └─── `description` | `string` | Yes | Description of the effect. |
| └─── `effectType` | `number` | Yes | Type of effect Possible values are: `0` (approve), `1` (deny) or `2` (pending, which means it require manual aproval/denial). |
| └`scoreInterval` | `object` | Yes | Defines acceptance and denial thresholds. The values are fixed as accept: 10 and deny: 5. |
| └── `accept` | `number` | Yes | Minimum score required to accept the rule. Fixed at `10`. |
| └── `deny` | `number` | Yes | Maximum score to deny the rule. Fixed at `5`. |
| └─ `authorizationData` | `object` | No | Defines required authorizers and whether all must approve. Supports both `Unit` and `User` authorizers. |
| └── `requireAllApprovals` | `boolean` | Yes | Condition that makes all authorizers approvals to be required. |
| └── `authorizers` | `array of objects` | Yes | List of entities that can authorize the action. |
| └─── `type` | `string` | Yes | Type of authorizer (e.g., `unit`, `user`). |
| └─── `id` | `string` | Yes | Unique identifier of the authorizer. |

---

### Response Example

``` json
{
  "id": "c20ececf-660f-4656-a802-9ba607e3585b",
  "name": "Dimension Monitoring - Dimension CRUD test - api.vtexinternal.com.br",
  "unitId": "Tech",
  "status": null,
  "priority": 1,
  "shouldSimulate": true,
  "ruleCollection": [
    {
      "id": "ad7742c2-8916-4bd1-86b3-b81f21f9db7e",
      "name": "Rule Monitoring test",
      "status": null,
      "priority": 1,
      "trigger": {
        "condition": {
          "conditionType": 1,
          "description": "Condition Description",
          "lessThan": 90,
          "greatherThan": 10,
          "expression": null
        },
        "effect": {
          "description": "Efect Description",
          "effectType": 2,
          "funcPath": null
        }
      },
      "timeout": 500,
      "notification": true,
      "scoreInterval": {
        "accept": 10,
        "deny": 5
      }
    }
  ],
  "creationDate": "2025-06-10T19:11:14.7103786Z",
  "creationVersion": "2.0.7",
  "creationEnvironment": "stable"
}

 ```

| Field | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `id` | `string` | ID of the created dimension. |
| `name` | `string` | Name of the authorization dimension. |
| `unitId` | `string` | Identifier of the business unit this dimension belongs to. |
| If this field is not provided in the request body, the value will default to the business unit associated with the user token from the `VtexIdclientAutCookie`. |  |  |
| `status` | `string` | Current status of the dimension (`null`, `accepted`, `denied`, `pending` and `ignored`). |
| `priority` | `integer` | Execution priority of the dimension. Lower numbers are evaluated first. Since all dimensions must be evaluated either way, priority may be hardcoded to `1` for all dimensions. |
| `shouldSimulate` | `boolean` | If true, the dimension is simulated and not enforced. |
| `ruleCollection` | `array` | Collection of rules contained in this dimension. |
| └─ `name` | `string` | Rule name. |
| └─ `status` | `string` | Rule status (can be null). |
| └─ `doId` | `string` | Optional ID of a Decision Object. |
| └─ `priority` | `integer` | Evaluation priority for the rule. |
| └─ `trigger` | `object` | Contains the trigger condition and effect logic. |
| └── `conditionType` | `integer` | Type of condition (e.g., `threshold`, `expression`). |
| └── `description` | `string` | Description of the condition. |
| └── `lessThan` | `number` | Optional upper threshold value. |
| └── `greatherThan` | `number` | Optional lower threshold value. |
| └─ `effect` | `integer` | Timeout in milliseconds for the rule. |
| └── `description` | `string` | Description of the effect. |
| └── `effectType` | `integer` | Type of effect (e.g., `accept`, `deny`, `pending`). |
| └── `funcPath` | `string` | Optional function path for custom effect logic. |
| └─ `timeout` | `integer` | Timeout in milliseconds for the rule. |
| └─ `notification` | `boolean` | Whether this rule should trigger a notification. |
| └─ `scoreInterval` | `object` | Score range for accepting or denying the rule. |
| `creationDate` | `string` | Date and time of dimension creation. |
| `creationVersion` | `string` | Version of the system that created the dimension. |
| `creationEnvironment` | `string` | Environment (e.g., `stable`, `beta`) where the dimension was created. |

